250 g Ground Turkey
2 unit Brioche Bun
2 tbsp Ranch Dressing
56 g Spring Mix
56 g Carrot, julienned
¼ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
66 g Mini Cucumber
1 tbsp Southwest Spice Blend
2 tbsp Oil*
0.31 tsp Salt*
2 tbsp Chipotle Sauce
3 tbsp Guacamole
0.13 tsp Pepper*
80 g Tomato

Before starting, preheat the oven to 425˚F. Wash and dry all produce.  Halve cucumber lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch half moons. Cut tomato into 1/4-inch rounds. Whisk together chipotle sauce and half the ranch dressing in a large bowl.

Add turkey, panko, Southwest Spice Blend and 1/4 tsp salt (dbl for 4 ppl) to a medium bowl. (TIP: If you prefer a firmer patty, add an egg to the mixture!) Season with pepper, then combine.  Form mixture into two 4-inch-wide patties (4 patties for 4 ppl).

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then patties. Pan-fry until patties are cooked through, 5-6 min per side.** (NOTE: After the patties are flipped, use a spatula to carefully re-shape them by pressing against the edges.) Transfer patties to a plate, then cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, halve buns. Arrange on an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up. Sprinkle cheese over top buns. Toast in the bottom of the oven until cheese melts and buns are golden-brown, 4-5 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)

Meanwhile, add carrots, cucumbers and spring mix to the bowl with dressing. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.

Spread guacamole, then remaining ranch dressing on bottom buns, then stack with patties and tomatoes. Close with top buns. Divide burgers and salad between plates.